## Review-feedback addendum (round 3: the in-process wire goes fully opaque)
Three Conductor comments on tests/conftest.py addressed:
1. (lines 64-71) The unknown-error_type catalog check now runs FIRST in _client_error_from_wire_payload, before the structured-rebuild dispatch.
2. (line 72) The unknown-type fallback no longer raises AssertionError: it returns client_errors.UnknownError(reason, payload) carrying the FULL wire payload -- production semantics for a newer server. UnknownError added to BOTH errors twins (contract: any client needs a degraded type for unrecognized wire errors). The registry-sync tripwire the AssertionError used to provide moved to tests/trace_server/test_contract_conformance.py::test_server_error_registry_names_only_client_known_types (within one repo the catalogs must agree; UnknownError is only a cross-version valve).
3. (lines 536-548) "We should not need to translate anything. The client and server are opaque to each other!" -- correct, and the twin-name reflection (_revalidate_twin: getattr by class name across the two tsi modules) was the offending scheme. Replaced with InProcessWireTraceServer: requests cross as plain dumped data and the SERVER edge materializes them via the types declared on ITS OWN method signatures (what FastAPI does in prod); responses cross as plain data and the CLIENT edge materializes them via the return types declared on ITS OWN TraceServerInterface/ObjectInterface protocols (what the bindings do in prod). Nothing inspects, names, or maps the other side's classes; a guard assert refuses to leak a server object when the client declares no model return. Python-mode dumps keep file-content bytes lossless (the real wire moves those via dedicated encodings, not model JSON). Streaming wraps iteration lazily, same as before; the cache-namespacing call.__name__ fix is preserved.
Verified at this level: conformance 26 passed (incl. the new registry-sync test); seam battery (weave_client, client_trace, annotation_feedback, digest_validation, evaluation_apis, trace_server) 242 passed; otel + isolated_client_executor 86 passed; ruff clean.

